	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm curious about the Shieldskin proc on the Blackhand Berserker Axe and since people aren't on that thread much I thought I'd ask here.<br><br>How does Shieldskin work ?&nbsp;&nbsp;Does it only take 40-50 pts of damage and then it's gone? Or does it take 40-50 pts per hit for a set amount of time.<br><br>If it's the former it's not a very good proc because one mob hit can easily be over 40-50 pts and it's done.  But if the latter is true, it might be nice because it could stop almost half the damage I'm taking for as long as the effect lasts.<br><br>Also, I'm assuming it's not like a lifetap where I get any HP's.<br><br>Any insight would be appreciated,<br><br>Thanks.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jun 18 13:38:41 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
