	   <tr><td colspan=2>Baking, or any tradeskills for that matter, is/are not a good way for newbies to make much pp.&nbsp;&nbsp;I would say farming some of the newbie/lowbie zones for spider/spiderling silks, bone chips, zombie skins,  MQ/HQ pelts, and selling them in the bazaar would get you started.<br><br>As it turns out, there are a lot of cheap int items for sale in the bazaar.   Get yourself a Black Alloy Medallion (bought mine for 375pp) and a Stein of Moggok (often sells for like 200pp).  That would be +15 int and Mana Preservation II for under 600pp.<br><br>Just my thoughts.  GL.  If you are on Bristlebane server, look me up, I would be glad to help out.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Apr 26 00:33:27 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>imakegood&nbsp;&nbsp;52nd Level Pally.  <br>Ialsomake    52nd Level Wizzy<br>Imakepets    21st Level Necro<br>Readyaim      17th LVL Ranger<br>Bristlebane Server. </td></tr>
