	   <tr><td colspan=2>BW <br><br>I hae been quaddding in BW for last few months and am now 55. I don't want to level so i have been getting aa xp at my level about 1/2 blue per quad. At 49 you may be borderline. <br>I use Shock of fore to pull, group em, BoF em, then hit with aoe ice ( I think pillar of ice ) and pillar of lighting. Lightning may be a higher level spell yet for you. <br>Go in from DL head N til you hit a trail. Follow trail down a hill and take a right. Straight to 4 dolumns, looks like a porch. Lots a lower level zone mobs in that area. Watch sarnaks -- some are casters and have sow. J boots are a must or sow potions. <br>every 4 or 5 pillars BOF em again. AND don't stop moving for more than a couple of seconds. Keep your eyes open when casting looking for which way&nbsp;&nbsp;your going to run and wandering mobs. <br>Good xp solo and loot is nice. There's better but its not bad with an occasional F loop tunics and stuff from giants.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
